-- Germany Still Seeking Europe-Wide Financial Transaction Tax, Ministry Says
-- B y   R a i n e r   B u e r g i n
-- 2010-10-19T13:53:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-19/germany-still-seeking-europe-wide-financial-transaction-tax-ministry-says.html
German Deputy Finance Minister Joerg
Asmussen said Chancellor Angela Merkel’s government still wants
the introduction of a Europe-wide financial transaction tax.  “As we have repeatedly said, the path is more difficult
than we imagined but we’re continuing to work on this,”
Asmussen told reporters in Luxembourg after a meeting of
European Union finance ministers.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
